The Saturnian measure was a sort of irregular iambic verse, said to have been origin- ally employed by Faunus and the prophets, who delivered their oracles in this measure. This was the most ancient species of measure em- ployed in Roman poetry ; it was universally used before the melody of Greek verse was poured on the Roman ear, and, from ancient prac- tice, the same strain continued to be repeated till the age of Ennius, by whom the heroic measure was introduced.
